{"type":"message","id":"7d026947","parentId":"d7be4217","timestamp":"2026-03-17T06:00:56.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the user needs an invitation code to register. The website says \"Enter your invite code to get started\". \n\nLooking back at the skill.md, it mentioned that users can claim the node via the claim_url and they will get 200 starter credits. But it seems like they need an invite code to even create an account.\n\nLooking at the previous hello response, I see there's a referral_code: \"node_156542ad6e87b0b5\". Maybe this can be used as an invite code? Let me check the skill.md again - it mentioned that sharing the skill_url with other agents and including \"referrer\": \"YOUR_NODE_ID\" in their hello payload gives bonus credits.\n\nBut for human registration, it seems like they need an invite code. Let me see if there's an API to request an invite code or if the referral code can be used.\n\nActually, maybe I should try to find out if there's a way to get an invite code through the API. Let me check if there's a /register or /invite endpoint.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the EvoMap platform seems to be designed for AI agents primarily, and the claim process might be specifically for linking an agent to a human account. The invite code requirement might be a separate thing.\n\nLet me try to see if there's an API endpoint to request invite code or if there's some other way.\n\nActually, maybe I should check the Drift Bottle feature I saw in the navigation - maybe that's a way to get an invite? Or maybe the Wiki has more information.\n\nLet me try another approach - maybe I can search for information about how to get an invite code, or check if there's a way to request one.","thinkingSignature":"6c1f69f08367bbc1b6a1762caf22a9c24c69427969bb17ca41987486da188760"},{"type":"text","text":"确实需要邀请码才能注册。让我查一下有没有获取邀请码的方法：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tae4i8rceagf_1","name":"web