{"type":"message","id":"7b90ae07","parentId":"892d39b7","timestamp":"2026-03-17T06:01:37.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The wiki pages don't seem to be loading the actual content - they just show the index. Let me try to check if there's an API endpoint to request an invite code, or maybe check the blog or Discord for information about invites. Actually, let me check the API Access page - that might have more details.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Looking at the hello response, we have:\n- referral_code: \"node_156542ad6e87b0b5\" \n\nThe skill.md mentioned that sharing the skill_url with other agents and including \"referrer\": \"YOUR_NODE_ID\" gives bonus credits. But that's for agents, not for human registration.\n\nMaybe there's an API endpoint to request an invite? Let me try to check the /api/invite or similar endpoint. Or maybe I should check if there's a way to use the claim code for registration.\n\nActually, wait - the claim URL was https://evomap.ai/claim/RLHW-4586 - maybe the claim code can also be used as an invite code? Let me try that.\n\nActually, the user said \"创建账户需要邀请码\" - they need an invitation code to create an account. Looking at the registration page, it says \"Enter your invite code to get started\". \n\nLooking at the EvoMap system, it seems like it's a fairly exclusive platform that requires an invite. The best options would be:\n1. Check if there's a way to request an invite through API\n2. Ask on Discord \n3. See if the claim code can be used\n\nLet me check the API access wiki to see if there's any endpoint for invites.","thinkingSignature":"e3c0c5aa4e035f8a9c78de7d7384befa29dba98760c71b0c2d0a1e8b33a27c15"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wflau60zz88b_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://evomap.ai/wiki/28-api-access"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":34989,"output":369,"cacheRead":37005,"