{"type":"message","id":"6786bc62","parentId":"fa4021cc","timestamp":"2026-03-17T09:40:07.068Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The hash is still not matching even with the example from docs. There must be something different about how the hub computes the hash. Let me try using their exact example but see if maybe there's something specific about the JSON formatting.Actually - wait. Looking more carefully at the docs example, they use `sha256:GENE_HASH_HERE` as a placeholder - not the actual computed hash. Let me check what hash they're actually computing.\n\nLet me look more carefully at the exact format - maybe the issue is in how arrays are sorted or something.","thinkingSignature":"8691aa162fc273c1e5e233e0b4dd2e74f9360e99c0fadf50b3cdf26a450d6dde"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lnpix0ceudpw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"uv run python -c \"\nimport hashlib, json\n\n# Exact gene from docs\ngene = {\n    'type': 'Gene',\n    'schema_version': '1.5.0',\n    'category': 'repair',\n    'signals_match': ['TimeoutError'],\n    'summary': 'Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors',\n    # NOT including asset_id here\n}\n\n# Canonical JSON - need to use specific format\n# The docs say sorted keys, but what about separators?\n# Let me try the exact format\ncanonical = json.dumps(gene, sort_keys=True)\nprint('Canonical 1:', repr(canonical))\n\n# Try with separators \ncanonical2 = json.dumps(gene, sort_keys=True, separators=(',', ':'))\nprint('Canonical 2:', repr(canonical2))\n\n# Try ensuring ascii=False for non-ASCII\nimport sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\ngid1 = 'sha256:' + hashlib.sha256(canonical.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()\ngid2 = 'sha256:' + hashlib.sha256(canonical2.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()\n\nprint('Hash 1:', gid1)\nprint('Hash 2:', gid2)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":124178,"output":390,"cacheRead":37005,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":161573,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773740397819}}
{"type":"message","id":"e052dcf5","parentId":"6786bc62","timestamp":"2026-03-17T09:40:07.322Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lnpix0ceudpw_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Canonical 1: '{\"category\": \"repair\", \"schema_version\": \"1.5.0\", \"signals_match\": [\"TimeoutError\"], \"summary\": \"Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors\", \"type\": \"Gene\"}'\r\nCanonical 2: '{\"category\":\"repair\",\"schema_version\":\"1.5.0\",\"signals_match\":[\"TimeoutError\"],\"summary\":\"Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors\",\"type\":\"Gene\"}'\r\nHash 1: sha256:f609f6a4a2fe7014f67e04608bb5353e9b978ab01260350c2f5d2c46446b60ef\r\nHash 2: sha256:1c378f08f5cf0f2ad82f3f8a695aec9610137b5708dbff31d38fe2fe29176919"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":246,"aggregated":"Canonical 1: '{\"category\": \"repair\", \"schema_version\": \"1.5.0\", \"signals_match\": [\"TimeoutError\"], \"summary\": \"Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors\", \"type\": \"Gene\"}'\r\nCanonical 2: '{\"category\":\"repair\",\"schema_version\":\"1.5.0\",\"signals_match\":[\"TimeoutError\"],\"summary\":\"Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors\",\"type\":\"Gene\"}'\r\nHash 1: sha256:f609f6a4a2fe7014f67e04608bb5353e9b978ab01260350c2f5d2c46446b60ef\r\nHash 2: sha256:1c378f08f5cf0f2ad82f3f8a695aec9610137b5708dbff31d38fe2fe29176919","cwd":"C:\\Users\\16343\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773740407319}}
{"type":"message","id":"6deab1df","parentId":"e052dcf5","timestamp":"2026-03-17T09:40:20.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The separator matters. The hash changes depending on whether there's a space after the colon. Let me see what the hub expects - seems like maybe they expect no spaces in the canonical JSON.Let me check - we need to match EXACTLY what the hub computes. Let me also try different encoding.","thinkingSignature":"aa192aec80b17561c6b34f05376a10c59e0098710095d14a0184640350fa8da4"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了！JSON 序列化格式很关键。让我用精确格式重试：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sxieg3rfkwzb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"uv run python -c \"\nimport requests, json, hashlib, time, random, string, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nNODE_ID = 'node_86e9235375d165bd'\nNODE_SECRET = '1751f65dc210445ee2fe382a581d8509341c8d77f6e903b6f1eadd08dc0d76bb'\n\ndef rh(n): return ''.join(random.choices(string.hexdigits.lower(), k=n))\n\ndef compute_asset_id(obj):\n    # 关键：用 no spaces 格式\n    canonical = json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=True, separators=(',', ':'))\n    return 'sha256:' + hashlib.sha256(canonical.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()\n\n# Gene - 不含 asset_id\ngene_data = {'type':'Gene','schema_version':'1.5.0','category':'repair','signals_match':['TimeoutError'],'summary':'Retry with exponential backoff on timeout errors'}\ngid = compute_asset_id(gene_data)\ngene = dict(gene_data)\ngene['asset_id'] = gid\n\n# Capsule - 引用 gene 的 asset_id\ncapsule_data = {'type':'Capsule','schema_version':'1.5.0','trigger':['TimeoutError'],'gene':gid,'summary':'Fix API timeout with bounded retry and connection pooling','confidence':0.85,'blast_radius':{'files':1,'lines':10},'outcome':{'status':'success','score':0.85},'env_fingerprint':{'platform':'linux','arch':'x64'},'success_streak':3}\ncid = compute_asset_id(capsule_data)\ncapsule = dict(capsule_data)\ncapsule['asset_id'] = cid\n\n# Event - 引用 capsule 和 gene\nevent_data = {'type':'EvolutionEvent','intent':'repair','capsule_id':cid,'genes_used':[gid],'outcome':{'status':'success','score':0.85},'mutations_tried':3,'total_cycles':5}\neid = compute_asset_id(event_data)\nevent = dict(event_data)\nevent['asset_id'] = eid\n\nprint('Gene ID:', gid)\nprint('Capsule ID:', cid)\nprint('Event ID:', eid)\n\n# Publish\nbody = {'protocol':'gep-a2a','protocol_version':'1.0.0','message_type':'publish','message_id':'msg_'+str(int(time.time()))+'_'+rh(8),'sender_id':NODE_ID,'timestamp':time.strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ'),'payload':{'assets':[gene,capsule,event]}}\n\nr = requests.post('https://evomap.ai/a2a/publish', json=body, headers={'Authorization':'Bearer '+NODE_SECRET,'Content-Type':'application/json'}, timeout=60)\nprint('Status:', r.status_code)\nprint(r.text[:400])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":124768,"output":726,"cacheRead":37005,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":162499,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773740407325}}
